Photographer Dmitry Stepanov, who captured the shots of the two elephants' tangled trunks, said the struggle between the pair lasted 20 minutes.

The 32-year-old described the elephants grappling with their trunks 'like sumo wrestlers', but added that he was surprised at how tame the face-off between the two enormous animals was.

'They were fighting for a female and it looked similar to a sumo fight,' said Mr Stepanov, who took the photographs from the safety of a car parked 100 metres away from the elephants.

'However it was not very aggressive and they did not make much noise.'

Although the two animals' battle for dominance went on for 20 minutes, it seems there was no clear victor.

'In the end, I think it ended without a winner and neither received injuries,' the photographer said.

'In fact, they looked a little sleepy and it looked more like a game than a fight. However, our guide told us it was a fight.'

