Mating among African elephants occurs every four years and can take place at any time of the year.

The elephants live in herds comprised of related females and their young. Male elephants leave the herd when they reach adolescence and maintain loose relationships with other males as they mature.

In later life they live alone, approaching females only during breeding season.

